  triage:title "Phase B plan self-contradiction: present tense at lines 65-67 vs past tense closure at 88-89" ;
  triage:description "docs/phase-B/phase-B-plan.md lines 65-67 self-contradicts the closure statement at lines 88-89. Lines 65-67 use present-tense framing ('currently starts') and state the numeric slot for sprint-B-homebrew is 'still open', but lines 88-89 state Phase B 'closed with' the recorded B.1-B.4 line plus sprint-B-homebrew, with 'no additional Phase B sprint scope remains open'. Remediation: rewrite lines 65-67 to past tense consistent with the closure statement, remove 'still open' framing." ;
